                "description": "Understanding what happens after our technician completes your HVAC service ensures you get maximum value:\n\nImmediate Post-Service (First 24-48 Hours):\n- System Testing: Technician will run your HVAC system for 15-20 minutes after service to verify proper operation, check temperature split (supply vs. return air), ensure all zones cool/heat properly (if zoned system), and verify smart thermostat integration works correctly.\n- Walkthrough & Education: Technician will explain what was serviced/repaired, why it failed or needed attention, how to prevent future issues, and answer all your questions about operation and maintenance.\n- Written Documentation: You'll receive detailed invoice showing exactly what was done, parts installed (with model/serial numbers), warranty information (parts and labor), and maintenance recommendations specific to your Gladden Farms home.\n- Digital Service Report: Within 2 hours, you'll receive automated email with full service report, before/after photos of work performed, and link to leave feedback about your experience.\n\nFirst Week After Service:\n- Monitor Performance: Your HVAC should maintain temperature easily throughout your home, run normal cycles (15-20 minute cycles in moderate weather, longer during peak heat/cold), provide consistent comfort upstairs and downstairs, and operate without unusual sounds or smells.\n- Warning Signs: Contact us immediately if you notice: warm/cold air from vents when system should be cooling/heating, short-cycling (on/off every few minutes), unusual sounds that weren't present before service, water leaking near indoor unit, or system won't maintain set temperature within 2-3°F.\n- Follow-Up Call: Our quality assurance team may call 3-5 days after service to verify your satisfaction and answer any questions.\n\nLong-Term Protection & Maintenance:\n- Parts Warranty: Manufacturer parts warranties typically range 1-10 years depending on component. Your invoice lists specific coverage for parts installed.\n- Labor Warranty: Our workmanship is guaranteed for 1 year from service date. If the same issue recurs due to our work, we'll fix it at no charge.\n- Maintenance Reminders: We'll send email/text reminders for your next recommended maintenance (typically every 6 months: spring AC tune-up, fall heating check).\n- Energy Monitoring: Watch your TEP or SRP bills over next 2-3 months. Properly serviced HVAC systems should show improved efficiency (lower kWh usage for same comfort level).\n- Filter Replacement: Remember to change filters every 30-60 days during peak season in Gladden Farms due to Marana's dust and desert conditions.\n\nGladden Farms Homeowner Tip: If you notice your utility bills remain high after HVAC service, contact us for a free energy assessment. Many Gladden Farms homes benefit from duct sealing, insulation improvements, or thermostat optimization—services we provide as part of our comprehensive home performance solutions.",
